body:
by **akidan**:

<pre>What steps will reproduce the problem?
1) View source for path.Visitor (src/pkg/path/path.go)
2) Note comment that reads:
// Visitor methods are invoked for corresponding file tree entries
// visited by Walk. The parameter path is the full path of d relative
// to root.
type Visitor interface {
    VisitDir(path string, f *os.FileInfo) bool
    VisitFile(path string, f *os.FileInfo)
}

What is the expected output?
&quot;full path of f relative to root.&quot;

What do you see instead?
&quot;full path of d relative to root.&quot;

What is your $GOOS?  $GOARCH?
darwin amd64

Which revision are you using?  (hg identify)
e004d329064a+ tip

Please provide any additional information below.
Go is awesome. :)</pre>
